Yes do whatever you feel is right!! My only advice is plan for anything to happen and do what is best for baby and you to be healthy.

I gave birth to my baby girl on Dec. 8th, a few days ago so it’s still fresh and here’s my story:

I planned to go all natural but then when my water broke but had no contractions, I had to be induced .. and then the Pitocin wasn’t working enough so I had to go over the max dose... and then I wasn’t dilating past 5cm after 24 hours of labour but I was in so much pain I was tired and miserable and thought I was going to die... so after being stuck at 5cm for 5 hours I broke and got the epidural even though I cried for hours fighting not to get it... then got an infection and fever for having a broken water for too long... but finally at 40 hours (thank god) I was at 9 1/2cm so they let me push b/c of the fever/infection so she had to come out fast or I was going to need a c-section. I only pushed for 30 mins and didn’t tear and baby girl did come out not looking so great b/c of the infection and I needed medical attention. I didn’t get delayed cord clamping, my bf didn’t get to cut the cord, & I didn’t get immediate skin to skin...

BUT she’s healthy! We’re both okay! And I can live with that and go through it all the exact said way to have her again!

So that’s my advice that I wish I understood before labour b/c I put my self through a lot of mental & physical stress trying to have it go as I had planned.

If you want babyG to come sooner walk a lot, do lounges going up stairs or ignore your doctor and let Alex touch you. If you know what I mean? Lol
My baby was just like yours. Throughout my pregnancy he was measuring big. I had already token the glucose test at 6 month. And I had pass it. But my doctor wanted to be sure. Cuz when you have diabetes will your pregnant that makes the baby to grow fast. So I had to take the glucose test once more time that came out that I had diabetes. But my doctor still wanted to be sure so I had to take the 3 hour glucose test. At that point I was scared. I didn’t want to do it. I was just like. Am almost 7 month; so once am 7 month let have him. Since that’s a save time have a baby.
But it come out that I was fine. So we kept track of how fast the baby was growing. Once I got to 38th weeks we agreed that At 39th weeks I would get induced. At that point he was weighing more then 8 lb. since I wanted to have vaginal birth we couldn’t have 10lb baby. But we also had talked about C-section in case I was having a hard time.
I when in to the hospital to get induced May 22th at 7:30pm. And every time a nurse or the student doctor came in to check in. They would ask me if I had an idea of how much the baby was weighing. And we would tell them that the last ultrasound they had told us he was weighing about a 8.5lb. Everyone would tell me. Oh no that wrong he looks more like a 7 lb.
Since the nurses and doctors were telling me that he was a 7 lb baby I was felling much better. But at the same time i was think about the conversation I have had with my doctor. That at some point I couldn’t do it I would have C-section. So when it came time. I asked for the epidural. I got it. Then right after I start pushing. I had a 20.5 in 9.5lb baby on May 23th at 7:19pm
I did rip down there lol. I also lost a good amount of blood. Not so much to the point where I had to get A blood transfusion. Everyone was amazed that I gave birth. Some doctor and nurses told me that I was supposed to get a C-section.
